article.headline: Loyola Marymount tops Northern Arizona 90-78
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Anthony Ireland scored 18 points and handed out 11 assists as Loyola Marymount beat Northern Arizona 90-78 Sunday night. After the Lions (4-0) jumped to an early lead, Northern Arizona responded with a 7-0 run and tied the score at 9-9 with 14:29 left in the half. The Lumberjacks later closed the half on a 6-0 spurt, all by Quinton Upshur, and headed into the break trailing 35-36. Max Jacobsen, who finished with a game and career-high 28 points, gave NAU (1-3) a 50-49 lead on a jumper with 14:14 remaining. The Lions, however, went on a 17-5 run capped by Evan Payne's steal and dunk, which extended Loyola Marymount's lead to 66-55 with 10:40 to go. The Lumberjacks wouldn't get closer than seven the rest of the way. Gabe Levin added 15 points and 10 rebounds for LMU. Upshur scored a career-high 25.
